<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="549" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1142,1529]" pageId="18" pageNumber="549">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1178,1204]" pageId="18" pageNumber="549">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Ozerov" authorityName="Ozerov. The" authorityYear="2011" box="[327,671,1179,1205]" class="Insecta" family="Scathophagidae" genus="Spaziphora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tomkovichi">
<emphasis box="[327,584,1179,1205]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="549">Spaziphora tomkovichi</emphasis>
Ozerov
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[686,766,1178,1205]" captionStart="FIGURES 52–56" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1891,1915]" captionTargetBox="[252,1346,230,1740]" captionTargetId="figure-15@19.[213,1375,181,1868]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 52–56. Spaziphora tomkovichi (Ozerov). 52, Male, lateral view; 53, Male postpedicel and pedicel, left lateral view; 54, Male palpus, left lateral view; 55, Male sternite V and terminalia, left lateral view; 56, Male sternite V and terminalia, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921443" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921443/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="549">Fig. 52</figureCitation>
) can be recognized by the following characteristics: anterior part of frons, face, parafacial, and gena whitish; postpedicel yellowish, with slightly angular upper corner (
<figureCitation box="[1339,1422,1214,1241]" captionStart="FIGURES 52–56" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1891,1915]" captionTargetBox="[252,1346,230,1740]" captionTargetId="figure-15@19.[213,1375,181,1868]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 52–56. Spaziphora tomkovichi (Ozerov). 52, Male, lateral view; 53, Male postpedicel and pedicel, left lateral view; 54, Male palpus, left lateral view; 55, Male sternite V and terminalia, left lateral view; 56, Male sternite V and terminalia, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921443" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921443/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="549">Fig. 53</figureCitation>
); palpi spatulate and white (
<figureCitation box="[445,530,1250,1277]" captionStart="FIGURES 52–56" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1891,1915]" captionTargetBox="[252,1346,230,1740]" captionTargetId="figure-15@19.[213,1375,181,1868]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 52–56. Spaziphora tomkovichi (Ozerov). 52, Male, lateral view; 53, Male postpedicel and pedicel, left lateral view; 54, Male palpus, left lateral view; 55, Male sternite V and terminalia, left lateral view; 56, Male sternite V and terminalia, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921443" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921443/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="549">Fig. 54</figureCitation>
); thorax black with grey dusting; legs yellow; abdomen slender, grey dusted, and subshiny; male sternite V ventrally with two distinct spur-like tubercles (
<figureCitation box="[976,1108,1286,1313]" captionStart="FIGURES 52–56" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1891,1915]" captionTargetBox="[252,1346,230,1740]" captionTargetId="figure-15@19.[213,1375,181,1868]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 52–56. Spaziphora tomkovichi (Ozerov). 52, Male, lateral view; 53, Male postpedicel and pedicel, left lateral view; 54, Male palpus, left lateral view; 55, Male sternite V and terminalia, left lateral view; 56, Male sternite V and terminalia, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921443" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921443/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="549">Figs 55, 56</figureCitation>
); male surstyli stout and apically pointed, closing each other (
<figureCitation box="[530,614,1322,1349]" captionStart="FIGURES 52–56" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1891,1915]" captionTargetBox="[252,1346,230,1740]" captionTargetId="figure-15@19.[213,1375,181,1868]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 52–56. Spaziphora tomkovichi (Ozerov). 52, Male, lateral view; 53, Male postpedicel and pedicel, left lateral view; 54, Male palpus, left lateral view; 55, Male sternite V and terminalia, left lateral view; 56, Male sternite V and terminalia, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921443" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921443/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="549">Fig. 56</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1142,1529]" box="[199,567,1359,1385]" pageId="18" pageNumber="549">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,343,1359,1385]" pageId="18" pageNumber="549">Body length</emphasis>
